(
<figureCitation id="13302A4AFFA6FF8CFF0381DAFEC2F6DA" box="[159,258,726,753]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2" captionStart-2="FIGURE 3" captionStart-3="FIGURE 4" captionStart-4="FIGURE 5" captionStart-5="FIGURE 6" captionStart-6="FIGURE 7" captionStart-7="FIGURE 8" captionStart-8="FIGURE 9" captionStartId-0="4.[151,250,1936,1960]" captionStartId-1="5.[151,250,1778,1802]" captionStartId-2="6.[151,250,1677,1701]" captionStartId-3="8.[151,250,1908,1932]" captionStartId-4="9.[151,250,1597,1621]" captionStartId-5="11.[151,250,1942,1966]" captionStartId-6="12.[151,250,1011,1035]" captionStartId-7="13.[151,250,1709,1733]" captionStartId-8="14.[151,250,977,1001]" captionTargetBox-0="[170,1436,575,1900]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1436,643,1755]" captionTargetBox-2="[151,1436,187,1654]" captionTargetBox-3="[151,1430,493,1885]" captionTargetBox-4="[151,1436,489,1574]" captionTargetBox-5="[170,1421,291,1919]" captionTargetBox-6="[151,1436,181,988]" captionTargetBox-7="[151,1436,345,1686]" captionTargetBox-8="[152,1437,313,950]" captionTargetId-0="figure-172@4.[151,1436,558,1910]" captionTargetId-1="figure-217@5.[151,1436,633,1755]" captionTargetId-2="figure-19@6.[151,1436,181,1654]" captionTargetId-3="figure-150@8.[151,1436,489,1885]" captionTargetId-4="figure-169@9.[151,1436,489,1574]" captionTargetId-5="figure-78@11.[151,1435,273,1919]" captionTargetId-6="figure-19@12.[151,1436,181,988]" captionTargetId-7="figure-101@13.[151,1436,345,1686]" captionTargetId-8="figure-79@14.[151,1437,309,954]" captionTargetPageId-0="4" captionTargetPageId-1="5" captionTargetPageId-2="6" captionTargetPageId-3="8" captionTargetPageId-4="9" captionTargetPageId-5="11" captionTargetPageId-6="12" captionTargetPageId-7="13" captionTargetPageId-8="14" captionText-0="FIGURE 1. A–B. Preserved female holotype and male paratype of Ceroys (Miroceroys) cancelloae sp. nov., from Extrema, Minas Gerais, Brazil. A. Holotype female V0034 in dorsal, lateral and ventral views. B. Paratype male V0033 in dorsal, lateral and ventral views. Scale bar: 10 mm." captionText-1="FIGURE 2. A–F. Head morphology of Ceroys (Miroceroys) cancelloae sp. nov. A, C, E. Holotype female V0034: A. Dorsal view; C. Lateral view; E. Ventral view. B, D. Paratype male V0033: B. Dorsal view; D. Lateral view. F. Paratype juvenile female V0032, lateral view.Abbreviations. Ant, antennomere; Bs1-Bs2, pro- and mesothoracic basisterna; Cx, coxa; Cxp, coxopleurite; Eye, compound eye; Fc, frontal convexity; Fem, femur; Frs1, prothoracic furcasternite; Fs, frontal suture; Gl, glossa; Md, mandible; Msn, mesonotum; Pd, pedicellus; Pgl, paraglossa; Plb, labial palpus; Pmx, maxillary palpus; Prn, pronotum; Sc, scapus; Sg, subgena. Scale bars: 1 mm." captionText-2="FIGURE 3. A–B. Metathoracic morphology of Ceroys (Miroceroys) cancelloae sp. nov., in dorsal view. A. Holotype female V0034. B. Paratype male V0033. Abbreviations. Cx, coxa; Cxp, coxopleurite; Epm, epimeron; Eps, episternum; Mds, median segment; Msn, mesonotum; Mtn, metanotum; Tg, tergite. Scale bars: 1 mm." captionText-3="FIGURE 4. A–F. Abdomen morphology of female Ceroys (Miroceroys) cancelloae sp. nov., holotype V0034, end of the abdomen:A. Dorsal view; B. Lateral view; C. Posterior view; D. Ventral view; E. Posterodorsal view; F. Terminalia, lateral view, subgenital plate spread by pins.Abbreviations. Ce, cercus; Ep, epiproct; Gap8-Gap9, gonapophysis 8 and 9; Gng, gonangulum; Gpl, gonoplac; Pre, praeopercular organ; Prp, paraproct; Sp, subgenital plate; St, sternite; Tg, tergite. Scale bars: 1 mm." captionText-4="FIGURE 5. A–E.Abdomen morphology of male Ceroys (Miroceroys) cancelloae sp. nov., paratype V0033, end of the abdomen: A. Dorsal view; B. Posterior view; C. Lateral view; D. Ventral view; E. Posterior view, detail of the terminal hook of the vomer. Abbreviations. Ce, cercus; Po, poculum; Prp, paraproct; St, sternite; St9a, anterior part of sternite 9; Tg, tergite; Tho, terminal hook of vomer; Tp, thorn pad; Vo, vomer. Scale bars: A–D = 1 mm; E = 0.5 mm." captionText-5="FIGURE 6. A–D. Egg of Ceroys (Miroceroys) cancelloae sp. nov., from the female holotype. A. Lateral view. B. Dorsal view. C. Anterior view. D. Detail of micropylar plate in dorsal view. Abbreviations. Mcup, micropylar cup; Mip, micropylar plate; MLi, micropylar line; Opc, operculum. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." captionText-6="FIGURE 7. A–D. Live habitus of nymphs of Ceroys (Miroceroys) cancelloae sp. nov., from Extrema, Minas Gerais, Brazil. A. First instar nymph, recently hatched. B. Third instar female nymph resting on fern. C. Fourth or fifth instar female nymph resting on fern. D. Three third instar nymphs, male (left) and two females (right). Arrows show protruding lobes on thorax and abdomen of females, arrowhead points to the absence of such structures in the young male nymph. Images not to scale." captionText-7="FIGURE 8. A–B. Live habitus of the female holotype V0034 of Ceroys (Miroceroys) cancelloae sp. nov., from Extrema, Minas Gerais, Brazil. A. Whole body. B. Detail of the head. Images not to scale." captionText-8="FIGURE 9. A–C. Paratype female MZSP810 of Ceroys (Miroceroys) cancelloae sp. nov. from Camanducaia, Minas Gerais, Brazil, displaying variations in ornamentation. A. Whole body of pinned specimen. B. Detail of the thorax in dorsal view. C. Thorax in lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531222" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531224" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531228" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531232" figureDoi-4="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531234" figureDoi-5="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531236" figureDoi-6="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531238" figureDoi-7="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531240" figureDoi-8="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531242" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6531222/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6531224/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6531228/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/6531232/files/figure.png" httpUri-4="https://zenodo.org/record/6531234/files/figure.png" httpUri-5="https://zenodo.org/record/6531236/files/figure.png" httpUri-6="https://zenodo.org/record/6531238/files/figure.png" httpUri-7="https://zenodo.org/record/6531240/files/figure.png" httpUri-8="https://zenodo.org/record/6531242/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="37">Figs 1–9</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
