<subSubSection id="C3116544FFA6FF8CFF5B878BFE5BF153" pageId="3" pageNumber="37" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB436CFFFA6FF8CFF5B878BFE5BF153" blockId="3.[151,1437,798,1653]" pageId="3" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B97FEADDFFA6FF8CFF5B878BFE8EF08A" bold="true" box="[199,334,1159,1185]" pageId="3" pageNumber="37">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is a patronym in honour of Dr. Eliana Marques Cancello, professor and curator of the entomological collection of the MZUSP and advisor of the masters of EBC and VMG, and soon probably of the upcoming master of PWE as well. Expert in termites and an excellent researcher and entomologist, she gladly advises our projects with phasmids, having already advised our colleague and friend P.I. Chiquetto-Machado on his PhD about phasmids and who also collected the new species. This comes in form of our sincerely gratefulness for supporting our goal to specialize in stick insects and of a recognition of her efforts on promoting research on 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D4CFFA6FF8CFF0B8652FEEBF153" authorityName="Jacobson &amp; Bianchi" authorityYear="1902" box="[151,299,1374,1400]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phasmatodea" pageId="3" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Phasmatodea</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="F31C765FFFA6FF8CFED38652FE57F153" box="[335,407,1374,1400]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="37">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3116544FFA6FF8CFF5B868EFB83F25F" pageId="3" pageNumber="37" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB436CFFFA6FF8CFF5B868EFB83F25F" blockId="3.[151,1437,798,1653]" pageId="3" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis id="B97FEADDFFA6FF8CFF5B868EFE82F1B7" bold="true" box="[199,322,1410,1436]" pageId="3" pageNumber="37">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D4CFFA6FF8CFE4C868FFCFAF1B7" authority="Crispino &amp; Ghirotto &amp; Engelking, 2022" authorityName="Crispino &amp; Ghirotto &amp; Engelking" authorityYear="2022" box="[464,826,1410,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Heteronemiidae" genus="Ceroys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phasmida" pageId="3" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cancelloae" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Miroceroys">
<emphasis id="B97FEADDFFA6FF8CFE4C868FFCFAF1B7" box="[464,826,1410,1437]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="37">Ceroys (Miroceroys) cancelloae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97FEADDFFA6FF8CFCDE868FFC5DF1B6" bold="true" box="[834,925,1411,1437]" pageId="3" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24C57A6FFA6FF8CFCDE868FFC5DF1B6" box="[834,925,1411,1437]" pageId="3" pageNumber="37" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be differentiated from the females of all other 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D4CFFA6FF8CFF4A86ABFE7CF1EA" authorityName="Piza" authorityYear="1936" box="[214,444,1447,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Heteronemiidae" genus="Ceroys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phasmida" pageId="3" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Miroceroys">
<emphasis id="B97FEADDFFA6FF8CFF4A86ABFE7CF1EA" box="[214,444,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="37">Ceroys (Miroceroys)</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the absence of crest-like longitudinal lobes on tergite III-VIII (
<figureCitation id="13302A4AFFA6FF8CFB7686AAFA86F1EA" box="[1258,1350,1446,1473]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[170,1436,575,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-172@4.[151,1436,558,1910]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–B. Preserved female holotype and male paratype of Ceroys (Miroceroys) cancelloae sp. nov., from Extrema, Minas Gerais, Brazil. A. Holotype female V0034 in dorsal, lateral and ventral views. B. Paratype male V0033 in dorsal, lateral and ventral views. Scale bar: 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531222" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531222/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="37">Figs 1A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13302A4AFFA6FF8CFACC86ABFA55F1EA" box="[1360,1429,1447,1473]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1908,1932]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,493,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-150@8.[151,1436,489,1885]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–F. Abdomen morphology of female Ceroys (Miroceroys) cancelloae sp. nov., holotype V0034, end of the abdomen:A. Dorsal view; B. Lateral view; C. Posterior view; D. Ventral view; E. Posterodorsal view; F. Terminalia, lateral view, subgenital plate spread by pins.Abbreviations. Ce, cercus; Ep, epiproct; Gap8-Gap9, gonapophysis 8 and 9; Gng, gonangulum; Gpl, gonoplac; Pre, praeopercular organ; Prp, paraproct; Sp, subgenital plate; St, sternite; Tg, tergite. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531232" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531232/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="37">4A–B</figureCitation>
) and the more lanceolate, thinner, and shorter meso- and metathoracic dorsolateral lobes (
<figureCitation id="13302A4AFFA6FF8CFB1886C6FB22F1CE" box="[1156,1250,1482,1509]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[170,1436,575,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-172@4.[151,1436,558,1910]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–B. Preserved female holotype and male paratype of Ceroys (Miroceroys) cancelloae sp. nov., from Extrema, Minas Gerais, Brazil. A. Holotype female V0034 in dorsal, lateral and ventral views. B. Paratype male V0033 in dorsal, lateral and ventral views. Scale bar: 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531222" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531222/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="37">Figs 1A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13302A4AFFA6FF8CFB7286C7FAD4F1CE" box="[1262,1300,1483,1509]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1677,1701]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,187,1654]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[151,1436,181,1654]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. A–B. Metathoracic morphology of Ceroys (Miroceroys) cancelloae sp. nov., in dorsal view. A. Holotype female V0034. B. Paratype male V0033. Abbreviations. Cx, coxa; Cxp, coxopleurite; Epm, epimeron; Eps, episternum; Mds, median segment; Msn, mesonotum; Mtn, metanotum; Tg, tergite. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531228" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531228/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="37">3A</figureCitation>
). Males can be differentiated from males of all other 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D4CFFA6FF8CFDC086E3FC83F222" authorityName="Piza" authorityYear="1936" box="[604,835,1519,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Heteronemiidae" genus="Ceroys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phasmida" pageId="3" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Miroceroys">
<emphasis id="B97FEADDFFA6FF8CFDC086E3FC83F222" box="[604,835,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="37">Ceroys (Miroceroys)</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the smooth, less robust, thinner meso- and metathoracic dorsolateral spines (
<figureCitation id="13302A4AFFA6FF8CFD91851EFDA8F206" box="[525,616,1554,1581]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[170,1436,575,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-172@4.[151,1436,558,1910]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–B. Preserved female holotype and male paratype of Ceroys (Miroceroys) cancelloae sp. nov., from Extrema, Minas Gerais, Brazil. A. Holotype female V0034 in dorsal, lateral and ventral views. B. Paratype male V0033 in dorsal, lateral and ventral views. Scale bar: 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531222" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531222/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="37">Figs 1B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13302A4AFFA6FF8CFDE8851FFD57F206" box="[628,663,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1677,1701]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,187,1654]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[151,1436,181,1654]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. A–B. Metathoracic morphology of Ceroys (Miroceroys) cancelloae sp. nov., in dorsal view. A. Holotype female V0034. B. Paratype male V0033. Abbreviations. Cx, coxa; Cxp, coxopleurite; Epm, epimeron; Eps, episternum; Mds, median segment; Msn, mesonotum; Mtn, metanotum; Tg, tergite. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531228" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531228/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="37">3B</figureCitation>
), the constricted abdominal segments, the tapering aspect of the cerci and the presence of short and conical dorsal spines, few smaller at the anterior region of mesothorax, and in pairs at the posterior region of each thoracic segment, with absence of further robust spines.
</paragraph>
